To get history of a git : git log
To get top 3 commits : git log -3
To get only commit-ids and commit messages : git log --oneline
To get only full commit-ids and commit messages : git log --pretty=oneline
To get full commits of a single file : git log --follow --all filename 
To get history of a commit : git show commit 
To get history of a commit in stat format : git show commit --stat
To configure user name : git config user.name “ourname”
To configure email id : git config user.email “our-email”
To edit the lastest commit message : git commit --amend -m “message”
To edit author for latest commit : git commit --amend --author “name <mail>” 
To commit the changes with prev commit : git commit --amend --no-edi
